title: Cyber Threat Intelligence Lead
description: As the threat intelligence lead for Firehost my work is focused on proactively seeking out cyber threat tactics and technical indicators of various threat group’s targets and tactics in order to better our security posture and better protect our customers. In this position I have the responsibility for leading, defining, and executing the security intelligence strategy for both the Cyber Threat Intel Team and our Cyber Threat Analytic Group. I am primarily responsible for analyzing security threats raised through the correlation and analysis of security events from sources such as firewalls, IDS/IPS devices, packet captures, logs, and private and government intelligence services. I also work to determine recommendations for mitigation, next steps for containment, or advisement/actions and combine that with the follow on post operation analytics that are needed for comprehensive threat intelligence. Additionally, I manage and focus our threat analysis capabilities, collection capability, intelligence and analysis technologies, and the development of any future advanced capabilities that will be used to protect our organization and our customers against existing and emerging threats.

This is a highly dynamic role and one that requires constant collaboration and initiative to meet the needs of a tight product launch deadline while striving to maintain the highest level of security possible for team CircleBack.

title: Cyber Research and Development Lead
description: At Accenture I lead the A-team of developers and researchers focused on a particular domain within our cyber security research and development lab group, namely security analytic operations and threat intelligence. We focus specifically on useful and innovative research paradigms and practices that look 3 to 5 years forward in order to aid our customers in systematically and intelligently augmenting their cyber security tools and practices as they grow their technology portfolio and their business gains momentum. I focus my team and research on understanding key technology trends in our client's domain and we work to match future opportunities to current and emerging challenges across cyberspace and the threat landscape. In this senior position I focus specifically on advanced security analytic development use cases and tailor them to meet client needs and technical specifications, coupled with this I manage the development of new and innovative proof of concept technologies and prototypes that touch on nearly every area of security analytic operations and cyber operations. We build real world tools and programs as well as innovative technical security models and methodologies that enable our clients and partners to better leverage their currently existing tools and security platforms to combat cyber threats as well as vastly improve their overall corporate security stance and system defense.

title: Chief of Cyber Analytics (Short Term Contract)
description: My position at DAC allowed me to lead and manage a variety of highly technical project and program offerings across the spectrum of cyber operations and advanced analysis techniques and technology. In this position I acted as the principal lead on several research and development efforts that advanced our clients understanding of intelligent cyber systems technology and operational cyber warfare for government and corporate customers both nationally and internationally. I also played an integral role as the technical development lead and Subject Matter Expert (SME) for a multi-million dollar research proposal that involved multiple corporate partners and was a first of its kind research and development project. My technical understanding of the space and my ability to lead drove our customers operational effectiveness and optimized their understanding and capability in cyber operations. Our team proposed and implemented initiatives to continuously improve the processes and architectures supporting defenses and analytic capabilities of our customers IT infrastructure, including incident handling and reporting tools and products. One of the most demanding and interesting projects required me to lead a team and assist in authoring a 100 plus page comprehensive paper on an innovative cyber workforce framework that has been adopted by a partner nation as its keystone cyber future framework initiative. This position truly required a broad understanding of the space and the ability to respond to a wide variety of technical and leadership initiatives while maintaining a sound business development record and contract management strategy.

title: Computer Network Exploitation Subject Matter Expert (Short Term Contract)
description: As the lead SME for the CNE/US SIGINT area of the JCAC program I served as the Subject Matter Expert for Computer Network Exploitation and Information Security for the Joint Cryptologic Analysis Course at Corry Station in Pensacola, Fl. This position was responsible for the training and curriculum development for the entire DOD cyber warfare education system, and afforded me the unique ability to both teach and lead a team of senior instructors and analysts in the technical development and inclusion of up to date exploitation and operational techniques to target and attack enemy networks. Functionally, this position required the use and expert knowledge of a variety of technical systems ranging from Metasploit and Armitage to Backtrack/EnCase as well as virtual machine systems and a variety of network architecture and system components. Added to this the position required the development of detailed technical products for training purposes and the development of scripting modules as necessary to improve the interaction of various network architecture pieces and hardware devices.

title: Chief Cryptologic Technician
description: As the NCOIC for numerous specialized work centers within NSA and the US Navy cryptologic service I directed all source research and development of cyber entities to comprehensively assess threat vectors, network forensics, and methodologies of nefarious cyber actors across the intelligence enterprise. Additionally my work defined and developed effective cyber defense strategies based on malicious cyber threat patterns and technology, enabling better understanding of possible relationships and factors for classification and attribution of threats. I both led teams and personally evaluated cyber threat actors and the possible uses and actions of targeted malware transmissions for possible kinetic cyber operations. My technical expertise documented and disseminated technical reports to boost forensic cognizance and understanding of cyber threats, along with the usage of malicious programs and malware. Other positions within this career field allowed me to institute the implementation of security incident and response mitigation actions to effectively remediate potential security exploits. I also acted as the senior cyber/DNI analyst for new mission threads; handled all DNI reporting, analytics, coordination, and research. Additionally, I conducted meetings and briefings in collaboration with analysts and senior members of intelligence community. My efforts led strategic execution of analysis with other intelligence community agencies, including Federal Bureau of Investigation, Treasury, Central Intelligence Agency, Defense Intelligence Agency, Office of Naval Intelligence, Transportation Security Administration, and Department of Homeland Security.
